Product DescriptionHere is the story of St. John Bosco's spiritual mentor in the priesthood and the man who influenced him to become a priest, told by St. John Bosco himself. St. Joseph Cafasso was called the "Priest of the Gallows" because he converted so many condemned criminals, often accompanying them all the way to their execution to keep alive in them the grace of final perseverance. Every minute of his life was consumed with the glory of God and the salvation of souls. St. John Bosco exclaims that he seemed to have been a full-time writer and a full-time pastor - judging by the fruit of his labor. In all, St. Joseph Cafasso is a striking example of how zealous are the saints in their work for Christ. Book Size: 7"x4" Softcover. 80 pp.
